# Task: walk forward

Make the robot walk **forward** (increasing world x position). You must produce exactly **4 Policy objects** that define one complete trot gait cycle. This cycle will be **looped automatically** for several seconds.

## CRITICAL: coordinate convention

In the body frame, **decreasing foot_x** moves the foot **forward** in the world. This is counterintuitive but correct for this robot model. To make the robot walk forward:
- Swinging legs must move foot_x **below** their neutral value (more negative = more forward in the world).
- Never move any foot_x above its neutral value — that moves the foot backward.

Neutral foot_x: front legs = +0.1934, rear legs = -0.1934.

## Gait structure

Two diagonal pairs take turns:
- **Pair A** = FL (row 1) + RR (row 2)
- **Pair B** = FR (row 0) + RL (row 3)

Ground level: foot_z = -0.27. Lifted: foot_z = -0.15 to -0.18.

## Walking pattern

**Phase 1 — Pair A reaches forward and lifts:**
Pair A (FL + RR) lifts off the ground and swings forward. Pair B (FR + RL) stays planted at neutral.
- FR: foot_x = +0.1934 (neutral), foot_z = -0.27
- FL: foot_x = +0.1634 (forward = below neutral), foot_z = -0.15 (lifted)
- RR: foot_x = -0.2234 (forward = below neutral), foot_z = -0.15 (lifted)
- RL: foot_x = -0.1934 (neutral), foot_z = -0.27

**Phase 2 — Pair A plants ahead:**
Pair A plants down at their forward positions. Body gets pulled forward.
- FR: foot_x = +0.1934 (neutral), foot_z = -0.27
- FL: foot_x = +0.1634 (forward, planted), foot_z = -0.27
- RR: foot_x = -0.2234 (forward, planted), foot_z = -0.27
- RL: foot_x = -0.1934 (neutral), foot_z = -0.27

**Phase 3 — Pair B reaches forward and lifts:**
Pair B (FR + RL) lifts and swings forward. Pair A stays planted.
- FR: foot_x = +0.1634 (forward = below neutral), foot_z = -0.15 (lifted)
- FL: foot_x = +0.1634 (forward, planted), foot_z = -0.27
- RR: foot_x = -0.2234 (forward, planted), foot_z = -0.27
- RL: foot_x = -0.2234 (forward = below neutral), foot_z = -0.15 (lifted)

**Phase 4 — Pair B plants ahead:**
All legs now at forward positions. Body pulled forward again.
- FR: foot_x = +0.1634 (forward, planted), foot_z = -0.27
- FL: foot_x = +0.1634 (forward, planted), foot_z = -0.27
- RR: foot_x = -0.2234 (forward, planted), foot_z = -0.27
- RL: foot_x = -0.2234 (forward, planted), foot_z = -0.27

## Constraints

- Step offset: 0.03 to 0.04 m **below** neutral foot_x. Example: front neutral +0.1934 → forward target +0.1534 to +0.1634.
- Swing lift: foot_z = -0.15 to -0.18.
- Never increase foot_x above neutral — that moves the foot backward in the world.
- Keep the gait symmetric between pairs.
- Keep the body level.

## Reward

R = -(|Δh| + |Δroll| + |Δpitch|) + distance_weight × x_distance

**Positive world x = forward = good. Negative world x = backward = bad.**

